      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much notice do I have to give to resign?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "You can resign at any time but you have to give the notice required by your employment agreement, or reasonable notice if it doesn’t have a notice period. What’s reasonable depends on things like how long you’ve been in the job and how senior your role is. \nAny annual leave taken during your notice period counts as part of your notice period. If you had no pre-booked leave, your employer might be entitled to refuse a request for annual leave during your notice period if they need you to hand over or finish things at work."
      }
