        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "You can’t be paid less or get worse work conditions because of your gender. If your boss discriminates against you, you can take a claim to the Employment Relations Authority or complain to the Human Rights Commission. \n[Employment Relations Authority https://www.era.govt.nz/; Human Rights Commission https://www.hrc.co.nz/]\n[Sources: Equal Pay Act 1972; Employment Relations Act 2000, s 103(1)(c); Human Rights Act 1993, s 22]"
