        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "You can take 3 days’ bereavement leave on the death of your partner, parent, child, brother or sister, grandparent or grandchild, or partner’s parent. If you have more than one bereavement at one time you can take the allowed amount of bereavement leave for each.\n[more]\nIf another person dies and your boss agrees this is a bereavement, you can take one day off, or more if they agree. They need to consider how close you were to the person, whether you need to help with the funeral, and whether you have any cultural responsibilities. You get paid your daily pay or average daily pay for each day you take off.\nUnlike annual or sick leave, there’s no maximum amount of bereavement leave you can take in any one year.\nYou need to tell your boss as soon as you can if you’re taking a bereavement day.\n[Source: Holidays Act 2003, ss 63, 64, 69, 70; http://communitylaw.org.nz/community-law-manual/chapter-19-employment-conditions-and-protections/bereavement-leave/]\n[FU: Want to know if you&#x27;re eligible for bereavement leave?: Leave - bereavement - eligibility]"
