        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "If you’re working on a foreign fishing boat in New Zealand waters, your wages must be paid into a New Zealand bank account in your name unless you agree otherwise. In any case your wages must be paid directly to you, while you’re in New Zealand. Your minimum wage is the New Zealand minimum plus NZ$2/hour. You must be paid for all hours you work, but always at least 42 hours per week. Your boss can only take specific costs out of your wages.\n[more]\n• food: this should be actual costs, up to a maximum of 10% of the minimum wage based on your hours worked\n• visa fees\n• airfares to and from New Zealand.\nThese deductions can’t make your wages less than the New Zealand minimum wage. Your boss can’t take out anything else e.g. lodging, entertainment or videos, health insurance and protective equipment or protective clothing. You can agree that you’ll pay your boss back money for personal expenses you ask for such as phone cards and cigarettes, but this must be in writing. \nCheck your employment agreement to find out how much your pay is and how it’s calculated. Remember, nothing in your employment agreement allows you to be paid less than the minimum wage above.\n[Source: www.employment.govt.nz/hours-and-wages/pay/minimum-wage/foreign-fishing-crews/]\nYou can contact the following organisations if you need further assistance: \n• MBIE for employment relations, pay and holidays information\n• the NZ company that charters your ship \n• the NZ Fishing Industry Guild union acts for fishing crews: www.nzfiguild.co.nz\n• International Transport Workers Federation may help if you&#x27;re in a member trade union: www.itfglobal.org/en\nVisa fees: https://www.immigration.govt.nz/new-zealand-visas/apply-for-a-visa/tools-and-information/tools/office-and-fees-finder\nFishing crew rights: www.immigration.govt.nz/new-zealand-visas/apply-for-a-visa/tools-and-information/work-and-employment/information-for-foreign-crews-working-in-new-zealand-fisheries-waters\n[FU: Want to know more about minimum wage rates?: Pay - minimum wage rates]"
