        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The pay period is the time you&#x27;ve been paid for in your pay. If you’re paid each fortnight, your pay period is two weeks. If you receive wages, you’re normally paid after the pay period (‘in arrears’). If you’re paid a salary you may be paid midway through the pay period, e.g. half in advance (before the work) and half in arrears.\nIf you don’t think you’re getting paid the right amount or on time, talk to your boss. If you’re not happy after that, contact MBIE for advice.\n[Source: https://www.employment.govt.nz/hours-and-wages/pay/pay-day/]\n[QR: Want to know more about when and how you should be paid?; Timing: Pay frequency; Ways to be paid: Pay method]"
