        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The minimum wage before tax from 1 April 2019 is $17.70 per hour ($141.60 per 8-hour day, or $708 per 40-hour week), or $14.16 per hour for a trainee or worker starting out ($113.28 per 8-hour day, or $556.40 per 40-hour week).\n[Source:https://www.employment.govt.nz/hours-and-wages/pay/minimum-wage/minimum-wage-rates/]\n[QR: Want to know more about minimum wage?; Starting/youth: Pay - minimum for starting out/trainee; Care &amp; support: Minimum wage for care and support workers; Agriculture workers: Minimum wage - agriculture; Fishing crews: Minimum wage - fishing crews; Exceptions: Minimum wage rates - exceptions]"
